    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-01-09T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-01-09T02:00:00-05:00" n="5"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d5">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/3121</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_DG1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Droppers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-01-09T09:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 9, 1917, 9 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received January 10, 8 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>219. My telegram No. 210 [<hi rend="italic">211</hi>], December 30.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d5fn1">
                        <ref target="frus1916Supp#pg_127">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1916, Supplement, p.
                        127</ref>.</note> Greek Government has submitted preliminary reply
                    conciliatory in tone but indefinite. Memorandum insists upon necessity of
                    effective assurances against encroachments, provisions for mixed commissions of
                    inquiry associated with question of reparation. Since establishment blockade
                    Provisional Government has seized several islands.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Droppers</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
